Target: `module/LLMWorkflow/retrieval/AnswerPlan.ps1`

Reason:
- prevent `Export-AnswerTrace` from reporting failure after a successful write because unlock in `finally` threw
- surface helper-command fallback failures in run/workspace resolution instead of silently disappearing

---

## Patch A: make lock release in `Export-AnswerTrace` non-destructive

Current code:

```powershell
finally {
    # Release lock
    if ($lockInfo) {
        $unlockCmd = Get-Command Unlock-File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
        if ($unlockCmd) {
            & $unlockCmd -Name "trace" -ProjectRoot $resolvedRoot | Out-Null
        }
    }
}
```

Replace with:

```powershell
finally {
    # Release lock
    if ($lockInfo) {
        $unlockCmd = Get-Command Unlock-File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
        if ($unlockCmd) {
            try {
                & $unlockCmd -Name "trace" -ProjectRoot $resolvedRoot | Out-Null
            }
            catch {
                Write-Warning "[AnswerTrace] Trace export completed, but lock release failed: $($_.Exception.Message)"
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Why this matters:
- without this patch, a successful file export can still surface as a failure if unlock throws in `finally`
- that is the exact kind of false-negative operational signal the remediation plan is trying to eliminate

## Patch B: add fallback visibility in `Get-AnswerPlanRunId`

Current code:

```powershell
if ($runIdCmd) {
    try {
        return & $runIdCmd
    }
    catch {
        # Fall through to generate new
    }
}
```

Replace with:

```powershell
if ($runIdCmd) {
    try {
        return & $runIdCmd
    }
    catch {
        Write-Verbose "[AnswerPlan] Get-CurrentRunId failed, generating fallback run ID: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    }
}
```

## Patch C: add fallback visibility in `Get-CurrentWorkspaceId`

Current code:

```powershell
if ($workspaceCmd) {
    try {
        $workspace = & $workspaceCmd
        if ($workspace -and $workspace.workspaceId) {
            return $workspace.workspaceId
        }
    }
    catch {
        # Fall through
    }
}
```

Replace with:

```powershell
if ($workspaceCmd) {
    try {
        $workspace = & $workspaceCmd
        if ($workspace -and $workspace.workspaceId) {
            return $workspace.workspaceId
        }
    }
    catch {
        Write-Verbose "[AnswerPlan] Get-CurrentWorkspace failed, using fallback workspace ID: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    }
}
```

## Patch D: add fallback visibility in `Get-WorkspaceContextForTrace`

Current code:

```powershell
if ($workspaceCmd) {
    try {
        $workspace = & $workspaceCmd
        if ($workspace) {
            $context.type = $workspace.type
            $context.packsEnabled = $workspace.packsEnabled
        }
    }
    catch {
        # Ignore errors
    }
}
```

Replace with:

```powershell
if ($workspaceCmd) {
    try {
        $workspace = & $workspaceCmd
        if ($workspace) {
            $context.type = $workspace.type
            $context.packsEnabled = $workspace.packsEnabled
        }
    }
    catch {
        Write-Verbose "[AnswerPlan] Failed to enrich workspace context for trace: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    }
}
```
